Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Backend Engineer* position with *Navan*. I bring over three years of professional experience designing and implementing high-performance backend services and distributed systems, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect the depth of API design, distributed architecture, and scalable code this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed and implemented high-performance API endpoints across 1,000+ platform endpoints, applying domain object modeling and rigorous input validation to translate complex business logic into clean, scalable backend services. I also architected a distributed multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph, enabling reliable coordination of backend processes at scale — and optimized backend concurrency and routing to reduce end-to-end latency by 60% and API costs by 50% in production. To ensure reliability across the full development lifecycle, I implemented a full observability stack using Langfuse and LangSmith for tracing, structured logging, and evaluation hooks. Prior to Sperse, at Qualitest, I contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform using React, Spring Boot, and AWS — designing high-performance backend services and API endpoints supporting a global user base across 30+ applications — and developed distributed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions to handle long-running data import jobs and prevent Lambda timeouts. Together, these roles have prepared me to contribute meaningfully to Navan's Expense team by building the backend engine that powers seamless, no-touch expense management for a global user base.

My academic and project experience reinforces my ability to operate with an AI-first mindset and extreme ownership across the full development lifecycle. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I managed end-to-end model development — from training on Pace University's HPC cluster using PyTorch and LoRA fine-tuning, to production deployment via vLLM and Hugging Face — and led workshops on AI Agents and CS fundamentals for 50+ students, bridging the gap between complex backend concepts and practical implementation. My Dark Factory project further demonstrates this ownership: it implements high-performance CLI IO via PTY with safe, auditable command execution and distributed, event-driven agentic loops broadcasting real-time updates across machines — the same kind of reliable, production-grade distributed backend thinking Navan's Expense platform requires.

I have always been passionate about AI-first product thinking and building systems that eliminate friction for real users — values that sit at the heart of Navan's mission to replace legacy T&E systems with a modern, consumer-grade experience. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration — I look forward to connecting!

